 inspire new and existing audiences Author cross-channel content, adapted to a wide range of audiences and channels Work collaboratively with our internal creative teams and external partners to craft campaigns, copy, and creative that drive audience growth and product downloads What you bring 2-3 years experience in social media, including a demonstrated track record in growing global communities through creative, engaging content Familiarity with Hootsuite, Sprout Social, or other social media tools Familiarity with Mailchimp, Contentful, and/or Google Analytics considered a plus An excitement for the power of narratives, and an understanding of what makes a clear and compelling story Demonstrated passion for social good \u2014 environmental and climate change experience a plus An understanding of the importance of grounding your ideas in data and analytics Curiosity, adaptability, and a sense of ownership towards your tasks A keen eye for detail in written, visual, and numerical content Native or near-native English (German is a plus!) We are committed to diversity and equity and seek to build an inclusive workplace that welcomes people from all different backgrounds. If you\u2019re looking for an incredible opportunity, a great place to work, and a chance to make a difference, we\u2019re excited to consider your application. A note on Covid-19 and WFH We want you to stay safe during the Covid-19 pandemic! We\u2019re currently working from home, and if you join us, we\u2019ll provide all the equipment you need to make your home office experience as productive and enjoyable as possible. Once everything is back to normal, we look forward to meeting you at our beautiful office in Berlin Mitte, featuring unlimited fresh fruits, delicious coffee, and a canteen with daily veggie options. Want to make remote a long-term thing? We\u2019re open to discussing that too. Apply for job Apply for job If this job interests you but you aren\u2019t certain if you meet all of theÂ